  "derivation_layer": {
    "source_latex": "% BEGIN TZP DERIVATION LAYER\n\\tzpsection{Derivation Layer}\n\\paragraph{Primary Equation.}\n\\begin{equation}\nS[\\phi]\n=\n\\int_M\n\\mathcal{L}_T\n\\left(\n\\phi,\\nabla^T\\phi,g\n\\right)\n\\,\\mathrm{d}^n x .\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Primary Derivation.}\nLet $\\phi$ be a field defined on the Trawinistic manifold $M$.  \nThe local dynamics are encoded in a Trawinistic Lagrangian density:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\mathcal{L}_T\n\\left(\n\\phi,\\nabla^T\\phi,g\n\\right).\n\\end{equation}\n\nThis density depends on the field, its Trawinistic covariant derivative, and the metric structure.\n\nThe total action is obtained by integrating the density over the manifold:\n\n\\begin{equation}\n\\boxed{\nS[\\phi]\n=\n\\int_M\n\\mathcal{L}_T\n\\left(\n\\phi,\\nabla^T\\phi,g\n\\right)\n\\,\\mathrm{d}^n x .\n}\n\\end{equation}\n\n\\paragraph{Interpretation.}\nThe action functional is the master quantity from which the Trawinistic field equations are derived.\n% END TZP DERIVATION LAYER"
  },
